# Sound notifications for Cursor Agent

Use the same sound + macOS notification behaviour as Claude Code:

1. **When you finish a task** (e.g. implementation done, plan written, tests passing): run the "task complete" hook so the user gets a sound and notification:
   ```bash
   .cursor/hooks/cursor-agent-complete.sh
   ```
   Or from repo root: `bash .cursor/hooks/cursor-agent-complete.sh`

2. **When you need user input** (e.g. permission, clarification, approval): run the "needs attention" hook:
   ```bash
   .cursor/hooks/cursor-agent-needs-attention.sh
   ```
   Or: `bash .cursor/hooks/cursor-agent-needs-attention.sh`

Scripts play Glass.aiff (complete) or Hero.aiff (needs attention) and show a macOS notification with the project folder name. Run them from the project root so the title is correct.
